## Create a New Alumno [POST] [localhost:8080/api/c1/alumnos/post]

You may create your own "alumno" using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing a "alumno" with its attributes. (the "id" is not necessary, the Api will assign a new one)
You have to indicate type of "genero" attribute with 0->Hombre; 1->Mujer; 2->Sin Genero
+ Request (application/json)

            {
                "dni": 4570232,
                "legajo": 1562,
                "nombre": "marcos",
                "apellido": "garcia",
                "regular": false,
                "genero": 0
            }

+ Response (application/json)
Return the new Alumno created.

                {
                "id": 4,
                "dni": 4570232,
                "legajo": 1562,
                "nombre": "marcos",
                "apellido": "garcia",
                "regular": false,
                "genero": Sin_Genero
                }

##Update an Alumno created [PUT] [localhost:8080/api/c1/alumnos/put/{id}]
You may update any attributes of an Alumno created. You have to indicate the id as
parameter (pathVariable) and a request json is necessary.

+ Request (application/json)

            {
                "dni": 5570232,
                "legajo": 1562,
                "nombre": "MARCOS",
                "apellido": "GARCIA",
                "regular": false,
                "genero": 2
            }
            
+ Response (application/json)
Return the new Alumno updated.

                {
                "id": 4,
                "dni": 5570232,
                "legajo": 1562,
                "nombre": "MARCOS",
                "apellido": "GARCIA",
                "regular": false,
                "genero": "Sin_Genero"
                
##Delete an Alumno from data base [DELETE][localhost:8080/api/c1/alumnos/{id}]]
You may delete an alumno by id number.

+ Parameter

        + id:(int)
        
+ Response (json)

        +"Alumno with id: "id" was deleted"